dcterms:creator: T. Pellissier Tanon
D. Vrandečić
S. Schaffert
T. Steiner
L. Pintscher
dcterms:description: Wikidata is a large knowledge base containing over 108 million entities about the world, actively maintained by the community, providing a compact and accurate form of world knowledge.
dcterms:title: Wikidata

dcterms:creator: A. Mallen
A. Asai
V. Zhong
R. Das
D. Khashabi
H. Hajishirzi
dcterms:description: PopQA is a natural language question answering dataset that requires long-tail Wikidata knowledge, converting knowledge triplets from Wikidata into corresponding natural language questions and answers.
dcterms:title: PopQA

dcterms:creator: B. Veseli
S. Singhania
S. Razniewski
G. Weikum
dcterms:description: The missing facts dataset contains factual triplets that are missing from Wikidata, with human-annotated ground truths, used to evaluate the ability of models to complete missing knowledge.
dcterms:title: Missing facts dataset

dcterms:description: D0 is a filtered version of Wikidata containing 46 million (subject, relation, object) triplets, focusing on relevant knowledge for common question-and-answer tasks.
dcterms:title: D0 (Filtered Wikidata)

dcterms:description: D1 is a subset of D0 containing a smaller number of triplets, used for evaluating the memorization capacity of language models.
dcterms:title: D1 (Subset of D0)

dcterms:description: DP opRel, DP opEnt, DT ailRel, and DT ailEnt are subsets of D0 focusing on popular and long-tail relations and entities, used to evaluate the performance of language models on different types of knowledge.
dcterms:title: DP opRel, DP opEnt, DT ailRel, DT ailEnt (Subsets of D0)

dcterms:creator: B. Veseli
S. Singhania
S. Razniewski
G. Weikum
dcterms:description: The general missing facts dataset is derived from the dataset released by Veseli et al., containing missing triplets and used for evaluating language models for knowledge base completion.
dcterms:title: General missing facts dataset (from Veseli et al.)
